seal     : Strategy is a game played in words — offers, threats, bluffs, treaties — for as long as both sides would rather keep talking than start killing. The art of war is game theory in practice; war itself is what happens when that game dissolves, when the bargaining range vanishes and might replaces the word. This sphere is about the dissolve: the exact point where the deal fails and the sword comes out.
